2. Project Objective

The primary objective of this project is to develop an intelligent quality management application that enables manufacturing organizations to:

Record manufacturing quality deviations accurately.
Assign investigation ownership.
Track investigation progress.
Manage containment actions.
Perform Root Cause Analysis (RCA).
Track Corrective and Preventive Actions (CAPA).
Generate AI-assisted quality summaries.
Draft automated follow-up communications.
Monitor deviations through dashboards.
Maintain complete audit trails.
Ensure quality compliance and timely closure.
3. Problem Statement

Manufacturing companies handle hundreds of production quality issues every month. These issues are often tracked using spreadsheets, emails, or paper-based systems, resulting in:

Delayed investigations
Incomplete deviation records
Missed due dates
Poor visibility into CAPA progress
Inefficient communication
Lack of accountability
Difficulty maintaining audit history
Compliance risks

An automated Manufacturing Quality Deviation Management System addresses these challenges by centralizing all quality-related activities and providing AI-assisted decision support.
4. Proposed Solution

The proposed solution is a web-based application that enables users to create, investigate, manage, monitor, and close manufacturing quality deviations through a structured workflow.

The system captures detailed deviation information, validates mandatory fields, identifies missing information, manages investigations, tracks CAPA activities, generates AI-assisted summaries, drafts follow-up communications, and provides dashboards for real-time monitoring.
Target Users

The application is intended for:

Quality Engineers
Production Supervisors
Manufacturing Operators
Quality Managers
CAPA Coordinators
Process Engineers
Plant Managers
Internal Auditors
Compliance Officers
System Administrators
